[build] Resolve _SupportLicense lazily inside _CopyExtractedMultiDexJar

Now that the Android SDK is extracted by `src/androidsdk` as part of the
same MSBuild invocation, the `Exists()`-conditioned `<_SupportLicense>`
property defined at file-load time resolves to empty on a clean build:
the m2repository directory does not exist yet when MSBuild evaluates
`Xamarin.Android.Build.Tasks.targets`. The downstream `<Copy>` then
silently no-ops on an empty SourceFiles and the following `<Touch>`
fails with MSB3375.

Move the `Exists()` check into `_CopyExtractedMultiDexJar` itself so it
runs after `src/androidsdk` has extracted the m2repository zip, and add
an explicit `<Error>` if the NOTICE.txt is genuinely missing instead of
silently producing an empty MULTIDEX_JAR_LICENSE later.

